questiontext.text: An 8-year-9 months old girl came with her mother to the RSGMP Orthodontic Clinic with a complaint that the maxillary front teeth were partially visible. Extra-oral examination symmetrical facial profile. Intra-oral examination, overjet -2 mm and overbite -2mm, crossbite of teeth 52,11,21,62 with teeth 32,31,41,42 accompanied by a mild central diastema of teeth 11, 21. In the maxilla, teeth 12 and 22 were not fully erupted. Mixed dentition and mesioocclusion molar relation. The cephalometric analysis showed a Class I skeletal pattern, with ANB = -1ø, SNA = 80, SNB = 81. What is the diagnosis in this case?
